      "body": "<a href=\"https://docs.hibernate.org/orm/current/userguide/html_single/#envers-mappingexceptions\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">The documentation</a> indicates that when you map a relationship as you have done and audit the host entity, Envers will create a join table for the audit data even though you&#39;re not using one to map the relationship itself.  Do you have such a join table? Are the parentIds recorded correctly there?"
